  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "What do you guys think of implementing macros/parameters/enumerations such that if there is some value being reused in the code, it is can be reused such that it's easier to read. Example:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nnull_addr: macro(address) = 0x0000...0000\r\ndef check_null(addr: address):\r\n    assert address != null_addr # replaced with 0x0000...0000 at compile-time\r\n```\r\n\r\nNot sure if that is the best syntax, but I hope you get the point.",
