    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "No code substitutions, just values. The resulting assembly would simply have hard-coded values of a given type in the spot where the parameter was in use. It makes it much easier for the reader to follow to have a parameter instead of hard-coded values in multiple positions within some contract code.\r\n\r\nBetter example:\r\n```python\r\nstake: num[addr]\r\nMAX_STAKE = num(1000)\r\n\r\ndef increase_stake(_stake_incr: num):\r\n    assert _stake_incr + self.stake[msg.sender] <= MAX_STAKE\r\n    self.stake[msg.sender] += _stake_incr\r\n\r\ndef move_stake(_to: address, _stake_amt: num):\r\n    assert _stake_amt + self.stake[_to] <= MAX_STAKE\r\n    self.stake[_to] += _stake_amt\r\n\r\ndef approve(threshold: decimal):\r\n    assert (self.stake[msg.sender] / decimal(MAX_STAKE)) >= threshold\r\n    selfdestruct(msg.sender)\r\n```",
